      %h2.govuk-heading-l
        Early Notice Letters (ENLs)
      %p
        Clean Air Zone local authorities, Defra and DfT (as JAQU) are Joint Controllers,
        which means that they jointly use personal data to ensure that people, who are likely to be
        affected by the introduction of Clean Air Zones, receive a letter giving sufficient
        advance notice of the zones coming into place. These letters are called ‘Early Notice Letters’.
      %p
        The relevant Clean Air Zone local authority, JAQU and DVLA will receive and use your personal data
        for the purpose of sending the Early Notice Letter to you.
      %p
        Your personal data that will be processed are:
        %ul.govuk-list-govuk-list--bullet
          %li
            %p
              the number plate (also known as a vehicle registration mark) of your vehicle,
              for which you are the registered keeper, that travels in a local authority Clean Air Zone
          %li
            %p
              the tax class of your vehicle
          %li
            %p
              and, in some cases as explained below, your name and address
      %p
        If your vehicle travels in a Clean Air Zone, the local authority’s automatic number plate recognition (ANPR)
        cameras covering that Zone will record your number plate, which the local authority will pass to JAQU
        so that JAQU can determine whether your vehicle meets current emission standards.
        If your vehicle does not meet these emission standards, DVLA will use your name and address
        held in their records with your vehicle number plate to send you a letter, on behalf of the local authority,
        informing you that you will likely have to pay a charge if your vehicle travels in that area after Clean Air Zone charging starts.
      %p
        The legal basis for the processing (use) of your personal data is that the use of your personal data is necessary
        for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest.
      %p
        The task in the public interest is to inform people of new regulations and penalties prior to their coming into effect.
        This relates to monitoring and identifying contraventions of Part III and Schedule 12 of the Transport Act 2000 and
        Parts 2 and 6 of The Road User Charging Schemes (Penalty Charges, Adjudication and Enforcement) (England)
        Regulations 2013 pertaining to the Clean Air Zone Charging Order relevant to the local authority
        whose ANPR cameras recorded your number plate.
      %p
        JAQU and the DVLA will not keep your personal data for the purpose of sending the Early Notice Letter
        after that letter has been sent to you.
